# Files/directories shipped in the packaged .vsix — allowlist shape.
#
# vsce reads this from the extension root. The default rule below
# excludes everything (`**`); the `!` rules below re-include exactly
# the paths the Marketplace bundle needs. Adding a new shipping path
# means an explicit `!` line here — there is no "implicit ship by
# absence of ignore".
#
# Rationale (Slice 7C release boundary): blacklist .vscodeignore is
# fragile under file growth. Every new dotfile or generated artifact
# at the repo root would silently ship unless someone remembered to
# add an ignore. Allowlist makes the bundle a closed set.
#
# When adding a new shipping path:
#   1. Add `!path` (file) or `!path/` followed by `!path/**` (directory).
#   2. The directory MUST be re-included before its children; vsce
#      cannot re-include a child of an excluded parent.

# Default: ignore everything.
**

# Runtime bundle — esbuild output consumed by VS Code at activation.
!dist/
!dist/**

# Marketplace metadata — vsce requires these at the extension root.
!package.json
!README.md
!LICENSE
!icon.png

# Versioning — root CHANGELOG feeds the Marketplace "Changelog" tab.
!CHANGELOG.md
